title: The Martian
overview: An astronaut becomes stranded on Mars after his team assume him dead, and must rely on his ingenuity to find a way to signal to Earth that he is alive.

title: Fitzcarraldo
overview: The story of Brian Sweeney Fitzgerald, an extremely determined man who intends to build an opera house in the middle of a jungle.

title: Children of Men
overview: In 2027, in a chaotic world in which women have become somehow infertile, a former activist agrees to help transport a miraculously pregnant woman to a sanctuary at sea.

title: Queen
overview: A Delhi girl from a traditional family sets out on a solo honeymoon after her marriage gets cancelled.

title: Inglourious Basterds
overview: In Nazi-occupied France during World War II, a plan to assassinate Nazi leaders by a group of Jewish U.S. soldiers coincides with a theatre owner's vengeful plans for the same.

title: Stagecoach
overview: A group of people traveling on a stagecoach find their journey complicated by the threat of Geronimo and learn something about each other in the process.

title: Big Fish
overview: A frustrated son tries to determine the fact from fiction in his dying father's life.

title: 2001: A Space Odyssey
overview: After discovering a mysterious artifact buried beneath the Lunar surface, mankind sets off on a quest to find its origins with help from intelligent supercomputer H.A.L. 9000.

title: Deliverance
overview: Intent on seeing the Cahulawassee River before it's dammed and turned into a lake, outdoor fanatic Lewis Medlock takes his friends on a canoeing trip they'll never forget into the dangerous American back-country.

title: Nebraska
overview: An aging, booze-addled father makes the trip from Montana to Nebraska with his estranged son in order to claim a million-dollar Mega Sweepstakes Marketing prize.

title: Spartacus
overview: The slave Spartacus leads a violent revolt against the decadent Roman Republic.

title: King Kong
overview: A film crew goes to a tropical island for an exotic location shoot and discovers a colossal ape who takes a shine to their female blonde star. He is then captured and brought back to New York City for public exhibition.

title: Blood Diamond
overview: A fisherman, a smuggler, and a syndicate of businessmen match wits over the possession of a priceless diamond.

title: Stand by Me
overview: After the death of one of his friends, a writer recounts a childhood journey with his friends to find the body of a missing boy.

title: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
overview: Harry, Ron, and Hermione search for Voldemort's remaining Horcruxes in their effort to destroy the Dark Lord as the final battle rages on at Hogwarts.

title: Dead Man
overview: On the run after murdering a man, accountant William Blake encounters a strange aboriginal American man named Nobody who prepares him for his journey into the spiritual world.

title: The Great Escape
overview: Allied prisoners of war plan for several hundred of their number to escape from a German camp during World War II.

title: Togo
overview: The story of Togo, the sled dog who led the 1925 serum run yet was considered by most to be too small and weak to lead such an intense race.

title: Life of Pi
overview: A young man who survives a disaster at sea is hurtled into an epic journey of adventure and discovery. While cast away, he forms an unexpected connection with another survivor: a fearsome Bengal tiger.

title: Barry Lyndon
overview: An Irish rogue wins the heart of a rich widow and assumes her dead husband's aristocratic position in 18th-century England.
